Byzantium being a ‘libera civitas,’ or a state whose freedom was secured by a Lex or a Senatus consultum, was freed from the duty of receiving a Roman garrison, and had the administration of justice (jurisdictio) ac- cording to its own laws, which in Greek is named αὐτονομία. Hence such a state is called on medals ἐλευθέρα καὶ αὐτονόμος.
